{"title_page": "Leon \u0218u\u0219man", "text_new": "'''Leon \u0218u\u0219man''' (June 10, 1910\u2013July 19, 1957)<ref name=\"Sighet\">{{cite web|url=http://www.memorialsighet.ro/1819-iulie-1957-intr-o-ambuscada-la-posaga-muntii-apuseni-sunt-impuscati-leon-susman-si-simion-rosa/|title=18/19 iulie 1957 \u2013 \u00eentr-o ambuscad\u0103 la Po\u0219aga, \u00een Mun\u021bii Apuseni, sunt \u00eempu\u0219ca\u021bi Leon \u0218u\u0219man \u0219i Simion Ro\u0219a|access-date=April 13, 2020|language=Romanian|website=memorialsighet.ro}}</ref> was a member of the Fascist paramilitary organization [[Iron Guard]] who, after the [[Soviet occupation of Romania]], became the leader of an armed [[Romanian anti-communist resistance movement|anti-communist resistance group]] in the [[Apuseni Mountains]].<ref name=\"romlib\">{{cite web|url=https://romanialibera.ro/special/documentare/cum-a-murit-seful-luptei-anticomuniste-din-apuseni-190859|title=Cum a murit \u0219eful luptei anticomuniste din Apuseni|newspaper=[[Rom\u00e2nia Liber\u0103]]|first=Claudiu|last=P\u0103durean|date=June 20, 2010|access-date=April 13, 2020|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n\u0218u\u0219man was born in [[Unirea, Alba|M\u0103h\u0103ceni]], [[Alba County]] on June 10, 1910, in a family of [[Romanian Greek Catholic Church|Greek-Catholic]] peasants. After   graduating with a Law degree from the [[Babe\u0219-Bolyai University|University of Cluj]], he practiced  law in [[Ocna Mure\u0219]] until May 15, 1948, when the [[Socialist Republic of Romania|Communist regime]] started to arrest ex-members of the Iron Guard and their sympathizers.<ref name=\"Anghel\">{{cite web|url=https://paginiromanesti.ca/2008/08/15/haiducii-demnitatii/|title=Haiducii demnit\u0103\u021bii|first=Viorel|last= Anghel|website=paginiromanesti.ca|\ndate=August 15, 2008|access-date=April 13, 2020|language=Romanian}}</ref>\nAt that time, he and his brother Gheorghe \u015eu\u015fman went underground, hiding from the authorities in the area [[Turda]]\u2013Ocna Mure\u0219\u2013[[Aiud]]\u2013[[Blaj]]. \n\nIn 1949\u20131950 \u0218u\u0219man led an anti-communist resistance group in the M\u0103h\u0103ceni\u2013Aiud area. During the period 1950\u20131957, he was the leader of the resistance group in the [[Po\u0219aga]] area, together with the Greek-Catholic priest Simion Ro\u0219a.<ref name=\"Sighet\" /> \n\nTo eliminate the \u0218u\u0219man resistance group, the Romanian security forces used informers against them and intercepted the correspondence of family members.<ref>{{cite journal|first=Andrei|last= Miroiu|year=2010|title= Wiping Out 'The Bandits': Romanian Counterinsurgency Strategies in the Early Communist Period| |journal=[[The Journal of Slavic Military Studies]]|volume= 23|issue=4| pages=666\u2013691|doi=10.1080/13518046.2010.526021}}</ref>  \u0218u\u0219man died in [[Po\u0219aga|Po\u0219aga de Sus]] of wounds sustained in a shootout with [[Securitate]] troops during the night of July 18\u201319, 1957.<ref name=\"romlib\" /><ref name=\"Sighet\" /> \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Susman, Leon}}\n[[Category:1910 births]]\n[[Category:1957 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Alba County]]\n[[Category:Members of the Romanian anti-communist resistance movement]]\n[[Category:Members of the Iron Guard]]\n[[Category:20th-century Romanian politicians]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Romania]]\n[[Category:Romanian Greek-Catholics]]\n[[Category:Babe\u0219-Bolyai University alumni]]\n[[Category:Romanian lawyers]]\n\n{{Romania-bio-stub}}\n", "text_old": "'''Leon \u0218u\u0219man''' (June 10, 1910\u2013July 19, 1957)<ref name=\"Sighet\">{{cite web|url=http://www.memorialsighet.ro/1819-iulie-1957-intr-o-ambuscada-la-posaga-muntii-apuseni-sunt-impuscati-leon-susman-si-simion-rosa/|title=18/19 iulie 1957 \u2013 \u00eentr-o ambuscad\u0103 la Po\u0219aga, \u00een Mun\u021bii Apuseni, sunt \u00eempu\u0219ca\u021bi Leon \u0218u\u0219man \u0219i Simion Ro\u0219a|access-date=April 13, 2020|language=Romanian|website=memorialsighet.ro}}</ref> was a member of the Fascist paramilitary organization [[Iron Guard]] who, after the [[Soviet occupation of Romania]], became the leader of an armed [[Romanian anti-communist resistance movement|anti-communist resistance group]] in the [[Apuseni Mountains]].<ref name=\"romlib\">{{cite web|url=https://romanialibera.ro/special/documentare/cum-a-murit-seful-luptei-anticomuniste-din-apuseni-190859|title=Cum a murit \u0219eful luptei anticomuniste din Apuseni|newspaper=[[Rom\u00e2nia Liber\u0103]]|first=Claudiu|last=P\u0103durean|date=June 20, 2010|access-date=April 13, 2020|language=Romanian}}</ref>\n\n\u0218u\u0219man was born in [[Unirea, Alba|M\u0103h\u0103ceni]], [[Alba County]] on June 10, 1910, in a family of [[Romanian Greek Catholic Church|Greek-Catholic]] peasants. After   graduating with a Law degree from the [[Babe\u0219-Bolyai University|University of Cluj]], he practiced  law in [[Ocna Mure\u0219]] until May 15, 1948, when the [[Socialist Republic of Romania|Communist regime]] started to arrest ex-members of the Iron Guard and their sympathizers.<ref name=\"Anghel\">{{cite web|url=https://paginiromanesti.ca/2008/08/15/haiducii-demnitatii/|title=Haiducii demnit\u0103\u021bii|first=Viorel|last= Anghel|website=paginiromanesti.ca|\ndate=August 15, 2008|access-date=April 13, 2020|language=Romanian}}</ref>\nAt that time, he and his brother Gheorghe \u015eu\u015fman went underground, hiding from the authorities in the area [[Turda]]\u2013Ocna Mure\u0219\u2013[[Aiud]]\u2013[[Blaj]]. \n\nIn 1949\u20131950 \u0218u\u0219man led an anti-communist resistance group in the M\u0103h\u0103ceni\u2013Aiud area. During the period 1950\u20131957, he was the leader of the resistance group in the [[Po\u0219aga]] area, together with the Greek-Catholic priest Simion Ro\u0219a.<ref name=\"Sighet\" /> \n\nTo eliminate the \u0218u\u0219man resistance group, the Romanian security forces used informers against them and intercepted the correspondence of family members.<ref>{{cite journal|first=Andrei|last= Miroiu|year=2010|title= Wiping Out 'The Bandits': Romanian Counterinsurgency Strategies in the Early Communist Period| |journal=[[The Journal of Slavic Military Studies]]|volume= 23|issue=4| pages=666\u2013691|doi=10.1080/13518046.2010.526021}}</ref>  \u0218u\u0219man died in [[Po\u0219aga|Po\u0219aga de Sus]] of wounds sustained in a shootout with [[Securitate]] troops during the night of July 18\u201319, 1957.<ref name=\"romlib\" /><ref name=\"Sighet\" /> \n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Susman, Leon}}\n[[Category:1910 births]]\n[[Category:1957 deaths]]\n[[Category:People from Alba County]]\n[[Category:Members of the Romanian anti-communist resistance movement]]\n[[Category:Members of the Iron Guard]]\n[[Category:20th-century Romanian politicians]]\n[[Category:Deaths by firearm in Romania]]\n[[Category:Romanian Greek-Catholics]]\n[[Category:Babe\u0219-Bolyai University alumni]]\n[[Category:Romanian lawyers]]\n[[Category:Romanian anti-communists]]\n\n{{Romania-bio-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Turgidson", "label": "safe", "comment": "removedCategory:Romanian anti-communistsusingHotCat(redundant)", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Leon_%C8%98u%C8%99man"}
